73174026.Name: Albert Einstein
73174026.CookingInstructions:
[ Preparation ]
Bar tools: cobbler shaker, jigger, funnel, strainer, bar spoon, ‘M’ ice stamp
Glassware: rock glass
Serving tools: Einstein book, Einstein bottle
Ice:  ice ball
Garnish: fresh thyme leave

[ Recipe ]
Opihr mix: 30ml
Cinzano Bianco: 30ml
Suze: 5ml
Tarragon - Cinzano Rosso: 20ml
Pineapple skin wine: 15ml
Lime juice: Dash

[ Method ]
Shake, Double strain 

[ S.O.P ]
1. Chill the Einstein bottle and rock glass (put them in the fridge)
2. Use the jigger to measure 30ml Opihr mix, 30ml Cinzano Bianco, 20ml Tarragon SV, 5ml Suze, 15ml Pineapple skin wine then pour into the cobbler shaker
3. Use the bar spoon to mix and taste
4. Add 3 nice ice cubes into the shaker (small size, medium size, biggest size on top)
5. Close the lid of the shaker and shake properly. Taste again after shaking
6. Put the funnel to the chilled Einstein bottle and double strain over the bottle, close the lid and put the bottle inside the book
8. Get the ice ball, use the ice stamp to create a ‘M’ logo on, put it into the chilled rock glass, garnish with a fresh thyme leave on top
9. Serve the drink (with a coaster) and tell the story to customers. Wish them happiness “Enjoy your drink please! Or Hope you will have a wonderful time with us!”
10. Come back to the table and ask for guest’s feedback

73176143.Name: Marie Curie
73176143.CookingInstructions:
[ Preparation ]
Bar tools: measure cup, jigger
Glassware: the tank 
Serving tools: Chemistry set, chemistry glasses, chemistry spoon, glass straw, long teaspoon, small metal cup, small towel (as coaster)
Ice: Crushed ice, Dried ice
Garnish: light, smoke from dried ice

[ Recipe ]
Pea butterfly Gin: 40ml
Shinny sake: 20ml
Pomegranate juice: 20ml
Shiso cordial: 20ml
Lime juice: 15ml
Sugar syrup: 10ml

[ Method ]
Build

[ S.O.P ]
1. Give to the guest the chemistry glasses (must be clean) upon order to surprise them
2. Prep. chemistry set, small metal cup and the light (wrap the light carefully & put it in small zip bag)
3. Pour 40ml Pea butterfly Gin and 20ml Shiny sake (shake well) to the biggest test tube
4. Pour 20ml Pomegranate juice, 20ml Shiso cordial, 15ml Lime juice, 10ml Sugar syrup into other different shaped tubes
5. Take the tank, put the wrapped light in the middle, turn the light on and fill the tank up with full crush ice
6. Place the biggest tube above the light, place other tubes around
7. Put the chemistry spoon & glass straw to the biggest tube and place the long teaspoon in the tank
8. Get 1 piece of dried ice, put into the metal cup and hide it under crushed ice
9. Hold the tank with the neatly squared folded towel placed below 
10. Get some boiled water into the measure cup and slowly pour it into the metal cup to create the smoke
11. Serve the drink, tell the story and explain ‘how to use’ carefully to the guest
12. Offer to take a cool picture for them. Wish them happiness “Enjoy your drink please! Or Hope you will have a wonderful time with us”
13. Come back to the table and ask for guest’s feedback

73176562.Name: Theodore Roosevelt
73176562.CookingInstructions:
[ Preparation ]
Bar tools: boston shaker, hand blender, jigger, funnel, strainer, fine strainer, bar spoon
Glassware: golden rim rock glass
Serving tools: MoM forest - deer horn holder 
Ice:  ice cube
Garnish: beef jerky, black pepper powder

[ Recipe ]
Shiitake mushroom Gin: 45ml
Beef jerky syrup: 15ml
Saffron extract: 3 drops
Lime juice: 15ml
Egg white: 1

[ Method ]
Shake, Double strain 

[ S.O.P ]
1. Chill the rock glass
2. Use the jigger to measure 45ml Mushroom Gin, 15ml Beef jerky syrup, 3 drops Saffron extract, 15ml Lime juice then pour into the small tin
3. Use the bar spoon to mix and taste
4. Take the bigger tin, break the egg to get egg white
5. Combine 2 tins and use the hand blender to blend the mixture
6. Add 4 nice and different sized ice cubes into the shaker (small size, medium size, biggest size on top) and shake properly
7. Taste the mixture again after shaking
8. Put 2 ice cubes into the chilled rock glass (the ice must not go over the rim of the glass) 
9. Use the strainer to double strain the mixture to the glass
10. Sprinkle the pepper powder on top (full light surface)
11. Place the glass on top of the holder, put 1 piece of beef jerky next to the glass
12. Serve the drink and tell the story, ask the customer to drink a bit first and then take a bite of beef jerky. Wish them happiness “Enjoy your drink please! Or Hope you will have a wonderful time with us!”
13. Come back to the table and ask for guest’s feedback

73176818.Name: Marilyn Monroe
73176818.CookingInstructions:
[ Preparation ]
Bar tools: boston shaker, hand blender, jigger, funnel, strainer, fine strainer, bar spoon
Glassware: sexy lady shaped glass
Serving tools: dress with bunny tail
Ice: none
Garnish: red cherry

[ Recipe ]
Wyborowa vodka: 40ml
Maraschino cherry: 15ml
Yogurt: 2 bsp
Beetroot-berry jam: 2 bsp
Double cream: 10ml
Sugar syrup: 10ml
Lime juice: 15ml
Egg white: 1

[ Method ]
Shake, Double strain 

[ S.O.P ]
1. Put the dress on the glass and chill it
2. Use the jigger to measure 40ml Wyborowa vodka, 15ml Maraschino cherry, 2 bsp Yogurt, 2 bsp Beetroot-berry jam, 10ml Double cream, 10ml Sugar syrup, 15ml Lime juice then pour into the small tin
3. Use the bar spoon to mix and taste
4. Take another tin, break the egg to get egg white
5. Combine 2 tins and use the hand blender to blend the mixture
6. Add 4 nice and different sized ice cubes into the shaker (small size, medium size, biggest size on top) and shake properly
7. Taste the mixture again after shaking
8. Use the strainer to double strain the mixture to the glass
9. Put a red cherry on top of the glass
10. Serve the drink (with a coaster) and tell the story to customers. Wish them happiness “Enjoy your drink please! Or Hope you will have a wonderful time with us!”
11. Come back to the table and ask for guest’s feedback

73263542.Name: Winston Churchill
73263542.CookingInstructions:
[ Preparation ]
Bar tools: mixing glass, bar spoon, jigger, strainer
Glassware: MoM ashtray
Ice: none
Garnish: chocolate cigar straw

[ Recipe ]
Johnnie Walker Black label: 20ml
Laphroaig 10yo: 10ml
Porto Cruz: 20ml
Leffe Brune syrup: 10ml

[ Method ]
Stir

[ S.O.P ]
1. Chill the ashtray and the mixing glass
2. Use the jigger to measure 20ml Johnnie Walker Black label, 10ml Laphroaig, 20ml Cruz Port, 10ml Leffe Brune syrup then pour into the mixing glass
3. Add 2 small ice cubes into the mixing glass at the bottom and 1 ice cube above
4. Use the bar spoon to stir the cocktail until cold. Slowly stir and taste to make sure the drink is not watery
5. Taste again after stirring, then place the strainer on top and pour the cocktail over the ashtray
6. Put a chocolate cigar straw on top of the ashtray
7. Serve the drink (with a coaster and a tissue glass) and tell the story to customers, tell them they can use the cigar as the straw and they can bite it slowly while drinking the cocktail. Wish them happiness “Enjoy your drink please! Or Hope you will have a wonderful time with us!”
8. Come back to the table and ask for guest’s feedback

73439090.Name: Breakfast Martini
73439090.CookingInstructions:
[ Preparation ]
Bar tools: parisan shaker, jigger, bar spoon, strainer, fine strainer
Glassware: tea cup with plate
Ice: ice cube with 'M'
Garnish: Dried orange

[ Recipe ]
TA Gin: 40ml
Black tea orange liqueur: 20ml
Lime juice: 20ml
Orange marmalede: 2 bsp
Sugar syrup: dash

[ Method ]
Shake, Double strain

[ S.O.P ]
1. Chill the tea cup
2. Use the jigger to measure 40ml TA Gin, 20ml Black tea orange liqueur, 20ml Lime juice, 2bsp Orange marmalede, dash of sugar syrup then pour into the shaker
3. Use the barspoon to mix and taste
4. Add 3 nice ice cubes into the shaker (small size, medium size, biggest size on top)
5. Close the lid of the shaker and shake properly.  Taste again after shaking
6. Double strain the mixture over the chilled glass
7. Garnish with 1 piece of Dried orange
8. Serve the drink (with a tea plate as coaster). Wish them happiness “Enjoy your drink please! Or Hope you will have a wonderful time with us!”
9. Come back to the table and ask for guest’s feedback.

73591858.Name: Bloody Mary
73591858.CookingInstructions:
[ Preparation ]
Bar tools: boston shaker, jigger, bar spoon, strainer, skewer, peeler
Glassware: oprah highball
Serving tools: straw
Ice: cube
Garnish: thyme, 2 olives, 1 pickle, 1 lemon peel, black pepper powder

[ Recipe ]
TA Vodka: 50ml
MoM black spiced sauce: 20ml
Tomato juice: 100ml
Tomato paste: 2 bsp
Lime juice: dash

[ Method ]
Rolling

[ S.O.P ]
1. Chill the glass
2. Use the peeler to get 1 piece of Lemon peel, cut it into nice shape and put it aside
3. Get 2 olives and 1 pickle, put them through the skewer. Get a bunch of thyme and set them aside
4. Use the jigger to measure 50ml TA Vodka, 20ml MoM black sauce, 100ml Tomato juice, 2bsp Tomato paste, dash of Lime juice then pour into the big tin
5. Use the barspoon to mix and taste
6. Add 3 nice ice cubes into the big tin
7. Place the strainer on top and rolling 4 - 5 times. Taste again after rolling
8. Double strain the mixture to the chilled glass and fill up with ice cubes
9. Add the straw, and put the garnishes on top. Sprinkle some black pepper powder on the surface
10. Serve the drink (with a coaster). Wish them happiness “Enjoy your drink please! Or Hope you will have a wonderful time with us!”
9. Come back to the table and ask for guest’s feedback.

73874622.Name: Negroni
73874622.CookingInstructions:
[ Preparation ]
Bar tools: bar spoon, jigger, peller
Glassware: Elvis Presley rock glass
Ice: ice ball with 'M'
Garnish: orange peel

[ Recipe ]
Bombay Gin: 30ml
Cinzano Rosso: 30ml
Campari: 30ml

[ Method ]
Stir

[ S.O.P ]
1. Chill the glass
2. Use the peeler to get a piece of Orange peel, cut into sexy shape and set it aside
3. Use the jigger to measure 30ml Bombay Gin, 30ml Campari, 30ml Cinzano Rosso then pour into serving glass
4. Add 2 small ice cubes into the mixing glass at the bottom and 1 ice cube above
5. Use the bar spoon to stir the cocktail until cold. Slowly stir and taste to make sure the drink is not watery
6. Taste again after stirring, then remove the ice
7. Get the ice ball with 'M' and dip it into the glass
8. Twist the orange peel to add the essence to the drink and dip it into the drink for garnish
9. Serve the drink (with a coaster). Wish them happiness “Enjoy your drink please! Or Hope you will have a wonderful time with us!”
10. Come back to the table and ask for guest’s feedback
